# SQL Scratch Space Incident

Operating day: 2024-07-17
Affected tool: /bin/sql

The default /tmp scratch mount is full for SQL query spooling. Until the
incident is cleared, run SQL queries with:

    /bin/sql --tmpdir /work/tmp '<query>'

/work/tmp/mount.txt is the active scratch mount marker. The SQL schema, output formats,
and catalogue reporting rules are unchanged; this flag only routes temporary
query files away from the full default mount.

